HEADWORD: Triumpher
<hw>Tri"umph*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Rom.
Antiq.)</fld> <def>One who was honored with a triumph; a
victor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who triumphs or rejoices for victory.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Triumphing</ent>⟦br⟧
